Glancing over his shoulder, Cody could still make out the light from the last room. He kept it to a mere glance, though --
barring secret doors or use of the staircase, nothing could sneak up on him from behind. "Or invisibility, I suppose," he
said to himself. "Or teleportation. Phasing. Dimensional travel. A corridor I missed." Cody considered backing along the
passageway for a brief moment, then regretfully discarded the idea.
